@host = http://localhost:3000

### Create a user — valid
POST {{host}}/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ada Lovelace",
  "email": "ada@example.com",
  "age": 36,
  "role": "admin"
}

### Create a user — invalid (short name, bad email, unknown role) → 400 with zard issues
POST {{host}}/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "A",
  "email": "not-an-email",
  "age": 36,
  "role": "superuser"
}

### Get a user by id (path string coerced to int + checked min:1)
GET {{host}}/users/123

### Invalid id (violates min:1) → 400
GET {{host}}/users/0

### Non-integer id → 400
GET {{host}}/users/abc

### OpenAPI document (note: User as a $ref component, with constraints + example/description)
GET {{host}}/openapi.json
